{
  "stem": "25591.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even when they were persecuted, when they were down, and so on, everything is better there and somehow they don't fit.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then there are people-- and these are the two extremes, and most people fall in between some place-- who love it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I took to the United States like duck takes to water.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I loved it from the day-- that's not true.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I loved it long before I arrived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and my love affair with America has grown since 1947.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, every morning-- we have a small apartment very near the capital, and my wife and I and our little dog walk to work.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when I look up, the dome and the flag, I choke up every morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "To have a penniless Jewish immigrant from Budapest, a survivor of the Holocaust, be given the privilege of serving in Congress and serving his area and the country is a reward nobody deserves.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I've always been public service-oriented.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When I got my bachelor's and master's degree at the University of Washington, then I went down to Berkeley and got my PhD in economics at Berkeley.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Even before I got it, I started teaching.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I already taught at the University of Washington.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I actually taught a few months after I arrived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I got myself a teaching position in-- at the University of Washington.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The only thing I was qualified to teach was Hungarian, and I persuaded the president of the university that the greatness of a university is measured by the variety of languages it teaches, and the only university that was teaching Hungarian at that time was the University of Indiana in Bloomington, and nobody else taught it.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
